According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Airline Catering market was valued at USD 18.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 19.8 billion in 2025 to USD 29.3 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 4.7% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing steady growth as increasing global air passenger traffic, expanding airline fleets, and rising demand for premium in-flight dining continue to drive investments in catering services. Airlines are increasingly focusing on enhancing passenger experience through high-quality meals, customized menu options, and innovative onboard food solutions while maintaining strict food safety and operational efficiency.
